@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 25, 2025</p>

<p>This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect the personal information of users who interact with our online learning platform, EduGate, developed using ASP.NET MVC.</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> When registering as a Student or Teacher, we collect your name, email address, and password.</li>
    <li><strong>Course Activity:</strong> We store your course enrollments, progress, reviews, and content submissions (for Teachers).</li>
    <li><strong>Learning Data:</strong> We track your progress through course content including video views, quiz attempts, and module completions.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<ul>
    <li>To manage user authentication and authorization.</li>
    <li>To display and update your dashboard with personalized learning data (e.g., enrolled/completed courses, content progress).</li>
    <li>To enable content creation and management features for Teachers.</li>
    <li>To improve our services through analytics of course interactions and content performance.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
<p>We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties. Your information may only be shared:</p>
<ul>
    <li>With other users as part of platform functionality (e.g., course reviews and teacher/course listings).</li>
    <li>If required by law, legal proceedings, or to protect the rights and safety of our users and the platform.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Your data is securely stored using SQL Server and managed via Entity Framework with proper access controls.</li>
    <li>Passwords are hashed and never stored in plain text.</li>
    <li>Access to sensitive operations (e.g., profile updates, content management) is restricted to authenticated users only.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
<ul>
    <li>You may update your email or password at any time from your profile page.</li>
    <li>Students can un-enroll from courses and delete submitted reviews.</li>
    <li>If you would like to request deletion of your account and associated data, please contact our support team.</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions or concerns regarding this policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@edugate.com">support@edugate.com</a>.</p>
